HEADWORD: Interpretative
<hw>In*ter"pre*ta*tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>interpr⟦eacute⟧tatif</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Designed or fitted to interpret; explanatory.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Interpretative</xex> lexicography.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>According to interpretation; constructive.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An <qex>interpretative</qex> siding with heresies.</q>
<rj><qau>Hammond.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Interpretatively</ent>⟦br⟧
